<! ------------------------------------------------------------------------>
<A NAME=HomePageProjectsDesc>
<H2>Research</H2></A>
<UL>
<LI><!WA3><A HREF="http://www.cs.rice.edu/~mpal/SC95/">
<B>Advanced compilation techniques for data-parallel languages</B></A><br>
We are developing a second-generation
<!WA4><A HREF="http://www.erc.msstate.edu/hpff/home.html">
High Performance Fortran (HPF)</A>
compiler to serve as a platform for experimental research on:
<UL>
<LI> <B>compilation techniques</B> for regular and irregular
     data-parallel applications,
<LI> optimization for message-passing, shared-memory, and hybrid
     <B>architectures</B>,
<LI> first-class compiler support for <B>programming tools</B>
     for performance analysis and data layout selection.
</UL>
<P>
<LI><!WA5><A HREF="http://www.cs.rice.edu/fortran-tools/DSystem/DSystem.html">
<B>Programming tools for data-parallel languages</B></A><br>
We are developing techniques and tools that enable programers to
understand and tune the performance of data-parallel applications without
having to understand the extensive, machine-dependent transformations
performed by a sophisticated, parallelizing compiler.  
Extensive cooperation between the compiler and performance tools is key to
providing the detailed, <I>source-level</I> performance feedback required 
in order to fulfill this goal.
</UL>

<P>
